    "_postman_id": "038ddf31-8c44-4860-955c-6de0c3ec7812",
    "name": "ExamDex API",
    "description": "# ExamDex API Documentation\n\nWelcome to the ExamDex API collection. This collection provides a comprehensive set of endpoints to manage the ExamDex platform.\n\n## Getting Started\n\n1.  **Environment**: Ensure you have the `baseUrl` variable set (default: `http://localhost:3001/api/v1`).\n2.  **Authentication**: Most endpoints require a Bearer Token. Log in as an Admin (`Auth > Admin Login`) to retrieve your `accessToken`.\n3.  **Authorization**: Include the token in the `Authorization` header as `Bearer <token>` for protected routes.\n\n## Modules\n\n-   **Auth**: Authentication for Admins and Students (OTP).\n-   **Users**: User management.\n-   **Classes**: Academic class management (e.g., Class 11, Class 12).\n-   **Exams**: Competitive exam management (e.g., JEE, NEET).\n-   **Subjects**: Subject catalog.\n-   **Chapters**: Chapter catalog linked to subjects.\n-   **Mappings**: Link Exams to Subjects and Subjects to Chapters with specific contexts.\n-   **Pricing**: Manage subscription tiers and credits.\n-   **Bulk Upload**: Excel-based bulk data ingestion.\n\n## Status Codes\n\n-   `200 OK`: Request successful.\n-   `201 Created`: Resource successfully created.\n-   `400 Bad Request`: Invalid input or validation failure.\n-   `401 Unauthorized`: Missing or invalid authentication token.\n-   `403 Forbidden`: Insufficient permissions.\n-   `404 Not Found`: Resource not found.\n-   `500 Internal Server Error`: Server-side issue.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
